# Verify before declaring done

Before reporting a task as finished, run the project's full quality gate
against the current working tree:

```bash
uv run ruff check .
uv run ruff format --check .
uv run mypy app
uv run pytest
```

All four must pass. If any of them fails:

1. Fix the failure if it was caused by your change. Auto-fixable lint
   issues should be repaired with `uv run ruff check --fix .` and
   `uv run ruff format .` before re-running the gate.
2. Leave the failure as-is *only* if it is a pre-existing failure on
   the base branch and unrelated to your change. In that case call it
   out explicitly in the final summary so it does not get silently
   accepted.
